verses.text_plain: Sing aloud unto God our strength: make a joyful noise unto the God of Jacob.
verses.verse_html:
1Sing aloud unto God our strength: make a joyful noise unto the God of Jacob. ▼
▼ of Asaph: or, for Asaph

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of Asaph: or, for Asaph

verses.text_plain: Take a psalm, and bring hither the timbrel, the pleasant harp with the psaltery.
verses.verse_html: 2Take a psalm, and bring hither the timbrel, the pleasant harp with the psaltery.

verses.text_plain: Blow up the trumpet in the new moon, in the time appointed, on our solemn feast day.
verses.verse_html: 3Blow up the trumpet in the new moon, in the time appointed, on our solemn feast day.

verses.text_plain: For this was a statute for Israel, and a law of the God of Jacob.
verses.verse_html: 4For this was a statute for Israel, and a law of the God of Jacob.

verses.text_plain: This he ordained in Joseph for a testimony, when he went out through the land of Egypt: where I heard a language that I understood not.
verses.verse_html:
5This he ordained in Joseph for a testimony, when he went out through the land of Egypt: where I heard a language that I understood not. ▼
▼ through: or, against

verses.text_plain: I removed his shoulder from the burden: his hands were delivered from the pots.
verses.verse_html:
6I removed his shoulder from the burden: his hands were delivered from the pots. ▼
▼ were…: Heb. passed away

footnotes.body_html: ▼ were…: Heb. passed away

verses.text_plain: Thou calledst in trouble, and I delivered thee; I answered thee in the secret place of thunder: I proved thee at the waters of Meribah. Selah.
verses.verse_html:
7Thou calledst in trouble, and I delivered thee; I answered thee in the secret place of thunder: I proved thee at the waters of Meribah. Selah. ▼
▼ Meribah: or, Strife

verses.text_plain: Hear, O my people, and I will testify unto thee: O Israel, if thou wilt hearken unto me;
verses.verse_html: 8Hear, O my people, and I will testify unto thee: O Israel, if thou wilt hearken unto me;

verses.text_plain: There shall no strange god be in thee; neither shalt thou worship any strange god.
verses.verse_html: 9There shall no strange god be in thee; neither shalt thou worship any strange god.

tokens.text: be in thee; neither shalt thou worship

verses.text_plain: I am the Lord thy God, which brought thee out of the land of Egypt: open thy mouth wide, and I will fill it.
verses.verse_html: 10I am the Lord thy God, which brought thee out of the land of Egypt: open thy mouth wide, and I will fill it.

verses.text_plain: But my people would not hearken to my voice; and Israel would none of me.
verses.verse_html: 11But my people would not hearken to my voice; and Israel would none of me.

verses.text_plain: So I gave them up unto their own hearts’ lust: and they walked in their own counsels.
verses.verse_html:
12So I gave them up unto their own hearts’ lust: and they walked in their own counsels. ▼
▼ unto…: or, to the hardness of their hearts, or, imagination

footnotes.body_text: ▼ unto…: or, to the hardness of their hearts, or, imagination
footnotes.body_html: ▼ unto…: or, to the hardness of their hearts, or, imagination

verses.text_plain: Oh that my people had hearkened unto me, and Israel had walked in my ways!
verses.verse_html: 13Oh that my people had hearkened unto me, and Israel had walked in my ways!

verses.text_plain: I should soon have subdued their enemies, and turned my hand against their adversaries.
verses.verse_html: 14I should soon have subdued their enemies, and turned my hand against their adversaries.

verses.text_plain: The haters of the Lord should have submitted themselves unto him: but their time should have endured for ever.
verses.verse_html:
15The haters of the Lord should have submitted themselves unto him: but their time should have endured for ever. ▼
▼ submitted…: or, yielded feigned obedience: Heb. lied

tokens.text: themselves unto him: but their time

footnotes.body_text: ▼ submitted…: or, yielded feigned obedience: Heb. lied
footnotes.body_html: ▼ submitted…: or, yielded feigned obedience: Heb. lied

verses.text_plain: He should have fed them also with the finest of the wheat: and with honey out of the rock should I have satisfied thee.
verses.verse_html:
16He should have fed them also with the finest of the wheat: and with honey out of the rock should I have satisfied thee. ▼
▼ finest…: Heb. fat of wheat

footnotes.body_html: ▼ finest…: Heb. fat of wheat
